begin_memory_text: we actually talked about earphones and wifi, lol. then we talked about the weather in Chicago and Houston. I shared my experience yesterday with the challenge of the wind gusts during our garden Halloween event.
middle_memory_text: We talked a lot about travel. My chat partner really loves traveling and he and his wife had travelled to Italy and we talked a bit about Italy. he also mentioned a trip to India and how the driving in both countries was really 'anything goes' compared to the US.
end_memory_text: We continued to talk about traveling and I shared a resource for eco-travel in Peru. We talked a little about the effects of Covid-19 and working from home, and also how its effect on our friends and families.
rest_of_day_open: I have a busy work schedule and need to finish some projects, so the rest of my week needs to be focused and efficient! I feel it's very easy for me to become distracted these days and am actually looking at ways to become more focused: meditation, yoga and perhaps some supplements.
critical_positive: The conversation worked well because my partner and I enjoyed talking about travel and had a lot to share! I also felt that we were both genuinely interested in learning about each other and appreciated this project giving us an opportunity to interface with strangers during this weird time. It was a respectful conversation.
critical_negative: Well, I sort of feel like I talked too much! I feel bad because I get excited about sharing and sometimes I can sense that i am talking too much. I wanted to ask my partner more questions. I have to work on this in general because I get feedback sometimes from friends and family that I talk too much. lol.

begin_memory_text: In the beginning, we talked about the weather in each of our respective towns.  My partner discussed the mild winters that were occurring in the past few years, while I disucssed how hot it is.  My partner also discussed their brother not enjoying the lack of seasons while living on the West Coast.
middle_memory_text: We talked about our travels and the change in cultures that are experienced.  My partner discussed living in Italy for eight years with their boyfriend.  I discussed my minor travels in comparison.
end_memory_text: We continued to chat about our travels and also discussed how COVID has made things very different.  We discussed an upcoming trip my partner had scheduled to Peru.  My partner gave me information to look it up at another time so I could show my wife.  Then, we talked about how changing how we consume news has brightened our days since COVID talk has turned everything very depressing.  Avoiding that has been helpful for both of us.
rest_of_day_open: This is my busy week at work so a lot of my time will be spent working on preparing and updating reports for the financial close.  Other than that, I will try to heal up and spend time outdoors with my spouse and kid.  Normally, we try to take a bike trip to the park so my kid can feed the fish and ducks.  Then, we'll prepare for another week of fun at work while maintaining distance from others.   Overall, it will be a busy but exciting week outside of work.
critical_positive: We both enjoyed talking about our travels and our personal experiences.  I think when we were both adding to the conversation, it made the time fly by and before I knew it, we had exceeded our time to chat.  Having a two-way conversation is one thing I think both of us did well.  We were able to easily change the topic, but the new topic related somewhat to the old topic.
critical_negative: I think when there was a point where I had nothing to add to her comment and I had to come up with something to continue our discussion.  That was a bit difficult, but overall I did not have any issues.  The video didn't lag but it was not very clear at points throughout our conversation.  I am unsure if it was on my end or not, but that did not take away from the conversation as I heard her just fine.
